The paper deals with the problem of finding an optimal route that satisfies certain constraints and covers a set of user-specified keywords. This problem involves techniques from database systems (cs.DB) for efficient query processing, information retrieval (cs.IR) for keyword matching, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for optimization, and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG) for algorithm design.
